df_cleaned = df_raw.copy()

#### CONVERT PRICE TO FLOAT #####

df_cleaned["price_new"] = df_cleaned.price.map(lambda x: (x.lstrip("$")))
df_cleaned["price_new"] = df_cleaned["price_new"].map(lambda x: x.replace(".00",""))
df_cleaned["price_new"] = df_cleaned["price_new"].map(lambda x: x.replace(",",""))
df_cleaned["price_new"] = df_cleaned["price_new"].map(lambda x: x.strip())
df_cleaned["price_new"] = df_cleaned["price_new"].map(lambda x: float(x))

#### CREATE AVG PRICE PER PERSON #####

#df_cleaned["price_per_person"] = round(df_cleaned["price_new"]/df_cleaned["accommodates"],2)

#### TYPE CAST NUMBER OF REVIEWS #####
df_cleaned["number_of_reviews"] = df_cleaned.number_of_reviews.astype("float")

####### EXTRACT BATHROOM COUNT FROM STRING ##############

bathroom_count_list=[]
for index,value in enumerate(df_cleaned.bathrooms_text):
    if isinstance(value,float):
        bathroom_count_list.append(np.nan)
    elif value == "nan":
        bathroom_count_list.append(np.nan)
    else:
        bathroom_count_list.append(df_cleaned.bathrooms_text.iloc[index].split()[0])

for index,value in enumerate(bathroom_count_list):     
    if isinstance(value,float): continue
    if value.isalpha():
        bathroom_count_list[index] = 1
    if "-" in value:
        bathroom_count_list[index] = 1
    else:continue  
        
df_cleaned["P_bathroom_count"] = bathroom_count_list
df_cleaned["P_bathroom_count"] = df_cleaned["P_bathroom_count"].astype("float")

#### CONVERT IS_SUPERHOST TO BOOL #####

df_cleaned.host_is_superhost = df_cleaned.host_is_superhost.map(lambda x: True if x =="t" else False )

#### CONVERT ISNSTANT_BOOKABLE TO BOOL #####

df_cleaned.instant_bookable = df_cleaned.instant_bookable.map(lambda x: True if x =="t" else False )

#### CREATE H_is_professional #####
df_cleaned["H_is_professional"] = df_cleaned["host_listings_count"]>= 2

#### CREATE NUMBER OF AMENITIES #####
mycounter = Counter()

list_ = []
for i in df_cleaned.amenities:
    i = i.replace("[","")
    i = i.replace("]","")
    i = i.replace("\"","")
    i = list(i.split(","))
    for idx,str_ in enumerate(i):
        i[idx] = str_.strip()
    mycounter.update(i)
    list_.append(len(i))

df_cleaned["P_number_of_amenities"] = list_
amenities_dict = (dict(mycounter))

#### CREATE TYPE  OF AMENITIES #####

##KEYWORD SEARCHER##
#for i in [ k for k,v in amenities_dict.items() if "Wifi" in k]:
#    print(i,amenities_dict[i])

##FREE PARKING

list_ = []
for i in df_cleaned.amenities:
    i = i.replace("[","")
    i = i.replace("]","")
    i = i.replace("\"","")
    i = list(i.split(","))
    list_.append(any([True for string in i if "Free" in string and "parking" in string]))
    #list_.append(any([True for string in i if "Free parking" in string]))

df_cleaned["P_is_free_parking"] =  pd.Series(list_)


##ElEVATOR

list_ = []
for i in df_cleaned.amenities:
    i = i.replace("[","")
    i = i.replace("]","")
    i = i.replace("\"","")
    i = list(i.split(","))
    list_.append(any([True for string in i if "Elevator" in string]))

df_cleaned["P_is_Elevator"] =  pd.Series(list_)

## COFFEE MAKER

list_ = []
for i in df_cleaned.amenities:
    i = i.replace("[","")
    i = i.replace("]","")
    i = i.replace("\"","")
    i = list(i.split(","))
    list_.append(any([True for string in i if "Coffee" in string]))

df_cleaned["P_is_Coffee_Maker"] = pd.Series(list_)

## WIFI

list_ = []
for i in df_cleaned.amenities:
    i = i.replace("[","")
    i = i.replace("]","")
    i = i.replace("\"","")
    i = list(i.split(","))
    list_.append(any([True for string in i if "Wifi" in string]))

df_cleaned["P_is_Wifi"] = pd.Series(list_)


############## CONSISTENCY - TESTS ##############
#df_cleaned.loc[:,["price","price_new"]].sort_values("price_new",ascending=False)


###### drop henceforth obsolete columns ######

######## FILTERING ##########
df_filtered = df_filtered.loc[(df_filtered.host_is_superhost == True)]
print(f"Afer filtering on is_superhost: {df_filtered.shape}")

#rating visibility (Zhang 2017 & more than 3 reviews) but also make sure that price can be taken as reliable subsitute of realized sale
df_filtered = df_filtered.loc[(df_filtered.number_of_reviews > 3)]
print(f"Afer filtering on reviews > 3: {df_filtered.shape}")

df_filtered = df_filtered.loc[(df_filtered.room_type != "Hotel room")]
print(f"Afer filtering out hotel rooms: {df_filtered.shape}")

df_filtered["price per capita"] = df_filtered.price_new / df_filtered.accommodates
df_filtered = df_filtered.loc[(df_filtered["price per capita"] > 5) & (df_filtered["price per capita"] <= 300),:]
#df_filtered = df_filtered.loc[(df_filtered.price_new > 10) & (df_filtered.price_new < 1000)]
#(df_filtered.price_new / df_filtered.accommodates).min()

print(f"Afer filtering out extreme listing prices: {df_filtered.shape}")

df_filtered = df_filtered.loc[(df_filtered.host_listings_count > 0)]
print(f"Afer filtering out 0 listing counts instances: {df_filtered.shape}")

df_filtered["log_price"] = np.log(df_filtered.price_new)

### Filling 220 missing values instances for bedroom with the avg. number of bedrooms at any given property capacity as measured by "accommodates"

bedroom_acco = round(pd.Series(df_filtered.groupby("accommodates")["bedrooms"].mean()),0)
for ind,val in enumerate(df_filtered.bedrooms):
    if val not in np.arange(1,17):
        df_filtered.bedrooms.iloc[ind] =  bedroom_acco[df_filtered.accommodates.iloc[ind]]

percent_missing = round(df_filtered.isnull().sum() * 100 / len(df_filtered),2)
abs_missing = df_filtered.isnull().sum() 
missing_value_df = pd.DataFrame({'column_name': df_filtered.columns,
                                 'percent_missing': percent_missing,
                                "abs_missing": abs_missing })

df_filtered.reset_index(inplace=True,drop=True)

missing_value_df.reset_index(inplace=True,drop=True)
print( "="*30+" df AFTER row filtering "+"="*30)
print(df_filtered.shape)
#display(missing_value_df.sort_values("percent_missing",ascending=False))

### RENAME COLUMNS ###

df_filtered = df_filtered.rename(columns = {"accommodates":"guest_capacity",

In [23]:
def fit_model(q,predictor):
    mod = smf.quantreg(reg_eq_string ,df_filtered_lf)
    res = mod.fit(q=q)
    return [q, res.params[predictor]] + \
            res.conf_int().loc[predictor].tolist()

QR Coefficient Assessment across quantiles in scope¶

In [24]:
## getting coefficient significances per quantile in quantile range

quantiles = np.array([0.1,0.25,0.5,0.75,0.9])
d = defaultdict(list)
d_r = defaultdict(list)

for i,q in enumerate(quantiles):
    mod = smf.quantreg(reg_eq_string ,df_filtered_lf)
    res = mod.fit(q=q)
    pv = round(res.pvalues,5)
    se = round(res.bse,3)
    coef = round(res.params,3)
    d_r[f"Model_{i}"] = [q,res.prsquared]
    s=list(zip(pv.index,coef,se,pv))
    for k,v,x,z in s:
        d[k].append((v,x,z))

pv_df = pd.DataFrame(d)

pv_df = pv_df.T
try:
    pv_df.columns = [f"QR={q}" for q in [0.1,0.25,0.5,0.75,0.9]]
except ValueError:
    pass

pv_df["Cross-QR Significance"] = [all(np.array([row[i][2] for i in range(pv_df.shape[1])])< 0.05) for index,row in pv_df.iterrows()]

sig_variables= pv_df.loc[pv_df["Cross-QR Significance"]]

model_df = pd.DataFrame(d_r).applymap(lambda x: round(x,2))
model_df["metric"] = ["Quantile","Pseudo-Rsquared"]
model_df=model_df.set_index("metric")

############# Results Print outs ############# 

### Predictors found to be significant across all quantiles  
print("="*5+"Significant Variables"+"="*5,"\n",pd.Series(sig_variables.index),sep="\n")

### Dataframe with tripartite tuples (Coefficient, Standard Error, p-value)
display(pv_df[1:])

### Model Results reporting Pseudo-Rsquared across models ### 
display(model_df)

row_counter = 0
for index,variable in enumerate(sig_variables.index):
    models = [fit_model(q,variable) for q in quantiles]
    models = pd.DataFrame(models, columns=['quantile', 'predictor_coeff', 'lb', 'ub'])
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].plot(models["quantile"], models.predictor_coeff, color='red', label='Quantile Reg.')
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].plot(models["quantile"], models.ub, linestyle='dotted', color='red',alpha=0.6)
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].plot(models["quantile"], models.lb, linestyle='dotted', color='red',alpha=0.6)
    
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].plot(models["quantile"], [reg_model.params[variable]] * n, color='blue', label='OLS')
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].plot(models["quantile"], [reg_model.conf_int().loc[variable][1]] * n , linestyle='dotted', color='blue',alpha=0.6)
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].plot(models["quantile"], [reg_model.conf_int().loc[variable][0]]* n , linestyle='dotted', color='blue',alpha=0.6)
    
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].fill_between(models["quantile"],models.lb,models.ub,interpolate=True,color="papayawhip",alpha=0.3)
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].set_ylabel("coefficient",fontweight ="bold")
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].set_xlabel("quantile",fontweight ="bold")
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].set_title (f"Subplot {index+1}: Coefficient Size across quantiles - {variable}",y=1.02)
    
    ax[row_counter,(col_counter+index)%2].legend(frameon=False,loc='upper center')

    if index%2 == 0:
        continue 
    if index%2 == 1:
        row_counter +=1
